<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="_Vha2Mse0EdmYjcUf1_oIew" name="finding_actors_and_use_cases_using_rsa,{06320FBA-D447-485E-97F5-24791C8E032C}" guid="_Vha2Mse0EdmYjcUf1_oIew" changeDate="2006-06-15T12:12:04.994-0700" version="7.1.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Overview&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This tool mentor assumes that a Use-Case Model has already been created in accordance with the &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../tech.rsa/guidances/whitepapers/model_structure_guidelines_for_rational_software_developer_DF8E00EB.html&quot;&#xD;
     guid=&quot;1.128046228219609E-305&quot;>Model Structure Guidelines for RSx&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The following steps are performed in this tool mentor:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a href=&quot;#Find%20Actors&quot;>Find Actors&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a href=&quot;#Find%20Use%20Cases&quot;>Find Use Cases&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a href=&quot;#Describe%20how%20Actors%20and%20Use%20Cases%20Interact&quot;>Describe How Actors and Use Cases Interact&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a href=&quot;#Package%20Use%20Cases%20and%20Actors&quot;>Package Use Cases and Actors&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a href=&quot;#Present%20the%20Use-Case%20Model%20in%20Diagrams&quot;>Present the Use-Case Model in Use-Case Diagrams&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a href=&quot;#Develop%20a%20Survey%20of%20the%20Use-Case%20Model&quot;>Develop a Survey of the Use-Case Model&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a href=&quot;#Evaluate%20Your%20Results&quot;>Evaluate the Results&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;a href=&quot;#MoreInfo&quot;>Additional Tool Information&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Find Actors&quot; name=&quot;Find Actors&quot;>Find Actors&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    After finding the actors, record your results as follows:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Open the Use-Case Model.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Navigate to a package where actors are to be captured. See &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../tech.rsa/guidances/whitepapers/model_structure_guidelines_for_rational_software_developer_DF8E00EB.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;1.128046228219609E-305&quot;>Model Structure Guidelines for RSx&lt;/a>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Create a diagram to capture actors, selecting use-case diagram for the diagram type. See &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot;&#xD;
        alt=&quot;help book icon&quot; src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Adding Use-Case Diagrams to&#xD;
        Models&lt;/i> in the online Help.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Add actors to the diagram.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Annotate each actor with a brief description. See &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot;&#xD;
        src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Documenting Model Elements&lt;/i>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot; src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; /> For more information,&#xD;
    refer to &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot; src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Modeling the&#xD;
    Behavior of a System&amp;nbsp;by Using&amp;nbsp;Use-Case Diagrams&lt;/i> in the online Help.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Find Use Cases&quot; name=&quot;Find Use Cases&quot;>Find Use Cases&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    After finding use cases, record your results as follows:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Navigate to a package in which use cases are to be captured. See &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../tech.rsa/guidances/whitepapers/model_structure_guidelines_for_rational_software_developer_DF8E00EB.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;1.128046228219609E-305&quot;>Model Structure Guidelines for RSx&lt;/a>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Create a use-case diagram to capture use cases. See &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot;&#xD;
        src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Creating Use-Case Diagrams&lt;/i> in the online Help.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Add use cases to the diagram. See &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot; src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot;&#xD;
        width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Adding Use-Case Diagrams to Models.&lt;/i>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Provide a brief description and the outlined flow of events. This can be initially annotated on the model element.&#xD;
        (See &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot; src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Documenting&#xD;
        Model Elements&lt;/i>.) Alternatively, you can use the RUP-provided template for &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_usecase_A5D30E62.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{B1526BC5-E346-42CB-A08A-3C0D7F382407}&quot;>Artifact: Use Case&lt;/a> and attach it to the use case in the model.&#xD;
        See &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot; src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Linking Model&#xD;
        Elements to External Files&lt;/i>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Describe how Actors and Use Cases Interact&quot; name=&quot;Describe how Actors and Use Cases Interact&quot;>Describe How&#xD;
    Actors and Use Cases Interact&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Describe the interaction between actors and use cases by following these steps:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Add previously created actors to the use-case diagram containing the use cases. See &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot;&#xD;
        alt=&quot;help book icon&quot; src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Adding Diagram Elements to&#xD;
        Modeling&amp;nbsp;Diagrams&lt;/i>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Add associations between actors and use cases. See &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot;&#xD;
        src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Specifying Relationships in&amp;nbsp;UML Diagrams.&lt;/i>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Optionally, describe the association. See &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot;&#xD;
        src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Documenting Model Elements&lt;/i>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Optionally, add multiplicity of a role. See &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot;&#xD;
        src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Specifying the Multiplicity Property&lt;/i>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Package Use Cases and Actors&quot; name=&quot;Package Use Cases and Actors&quot;>Package Use Cases and Actors&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Organize actors and use cases in packages.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Refer to &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot; src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Organizing&#xD;
    Model Elements in Packages&lt;/i> in the online Help.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Present the Use-Case Model in Diagrams&quot; name=&quot;Present the Use-Case Model in Diagrams&quot;>Present the Use-Case Model&#xD;
    in Use-Case Diagrams&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For the purposes of this tool mentor, it is assumed that diagrams have been created as actors and use cases are&#xD;
    identified. See earlier steps for guidance on use-case diagramming.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Develop a Survey of the Use-Case Model&quot; name=&quot;Develop a Survey of the Use-Case Model&quot;>Develop a Survey of the&#xD;
    Use-Case Model&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The tool&amp;nbsp;provides Use-Case Model reports. It might be helpful to publish the model to HTML format. Also note that&#xD;
    diagrams can be copied to Microsoft Word and other programs.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For more information, refer to &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot; src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot;&#xD;
    width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Publishing Models&lt;/i>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Evaluate Your Results&quot; name=&quot;Evaluate Your Results&quot;>Evaluate the Results&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Reports (see previous step) and published models can be useful for reviewing the model.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For more information, refer to &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot; src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot;&#xD;
    width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Publishing Models&lt;/i> and to the &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot;&#xD;
    src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Publishing a Model to Web&lt;/i> tutorial.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;MoreInfo&quot; name=&quot;MoreInfo&quot;>Additional Tool Information&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Samples:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot; src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>&amp;nbsp;UML Models -&#xD;
        Simple UML Model&lt;/i>&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
